=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: React 4-chloropyrimidine (or the corresponding chlorodiazine matching the c2ccncn2 fragment) with 3,4-dimethoxybenzylamine to give the secondary amine intermediate HN(Cc1ccc(OC)cc1OC)c2ccncn2. | Step 2: Sulfonylate that amine with 2,4,5-trifluorobenzenesulfonyl chloride to form the aryl sulfonamide Ar-SO2N(Cc1ccc(OC)cc1OC)c2ccncn2 (Ar = 2,4,5-trifluorophenyl). | Step 3: Take enantiopure trans-4-hydroxy-1-(1-ethyl-1H-pyrazol-4-yl)cyclohexane ((1R,4S)/(1S,4R) as required), deprotonate with NaH or Cs2CO3, and perform SNAr on the remaining activated aryl fluoride of the sulfonamide from Step 2 to install the cyclohexyl oxy group, giving CCn1nccc1[C@H]1CCC[C@@H]1Oc1cc(F)c(S(=O)(=O)N(Cc2ccc(OC)cc2OC)c2ccncn2)cc1F.

